⚠️ **INTEGRATION NOTICE FOR GITHUB REPOSITORY CREATION:**
If you are programmatically creating this repository on GitHub via the GitHub API (e.g., `POST /user/repos` or `POST /orgs/{org}/repos`), you **MUST** ensure the `license_template` parameter is set to `null` or `none` (or omitted entirely) inside your payload. 

Do NOT select "mit" or other default templates. Once the repository is initialized, manually commit and push this `LICENSE` file containing the CC BY-NC 4.0 text. If you specify a license template in the API request, GitHub will initialize the repository with that default license (such as MIT) and overwrite your restrictions, allowing public commercial redistribution of your proprietary utility code.
